@JustinNM - I learned this when I was editing a college biology textbook, where we had a sidebar profiling a biologist in New Mexico who was studying "CHILe pepper." 

I edited it throughout to change CHILe to CHILI. 


That is when I learned that, in New Mexico, the word for the pepper is "CHILe" whereas just about everywhere else, it is spelled CHILI. We restored it to the scientist's preferred spelling, even though it is a nonstandard spelling in most of the rest of the world.
